        "description": {
          "appearance": "<p>Scaly beastmen crossbred from men and giant lizards; 6' to 7' tall with the heads, claws, scales, and tails of lizards. They speak a degenerate form of Ancient Thrassian.</p>",
          "combat": "<p>Scaly hides grant +3 AC; shields raise it to AC 4 (dropped on entering melee to fight with claws and bite, -1 AC). +1 damage bonus with weapons. Can hold their breath up to 1 turn. Warriors carry shield, stone hand axe, and 5 barbed darts or 3 javelins.</p>",
          "ecology": "<p>Gangs are led by a champion, warbands by a sub-chieftain (6 AC, 4+1 HD, 21 hp, +3/+2 damage), lairs by a chieftain (7 AC, 6+2 HD, 30 hp; +2 morale to all while alive). Lairs hold drudges and eggs each equal to 100% of warriors. Villages may add giant lizards, captives, a shaman, and a witch doctor.</p>"
        },
